description: Coefficients of monic primitive irreducible polynomials over GF(3) listed in lexicographic order.
references: R. Church, Tables of irreducible polynomials for the first four prime moduli, Annals Math., 36 (1935), 198-209.
links: T. D. Noe, Table of n, a(n) for n=1..561 (through degree 8)
example: The first few are x+1; x^2+x+2, x^2+2x+2; ...
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_, Jan 13 2001
extensions: More terms from Jean Gaumont (jeangaum87(AT)yahoo.com), Apr 16 2006
